Description: Disc foot and wall sherd of Attic black-glazed pottery closed vessel (amphora or oinochoe); central sinking on underside; glazed black on exterior and top and outside of foot; reserved underside; part of an added red band at top of outside of foot; inscription cut on underside.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 493)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 675, no. 338)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.0921)
